3. Variables and types of Variables in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Variables is ntg but name that used to refer to a piece of information or data. This data can be of any type, such as number, string, boolean, etc.
ğŸ‘‰ We can reuse this data across screens throughout the app.
ğŸ”¹ Types of Variables:
1. Context Variables (UpdateContext): Scoped only to the current screen, created via UpdateContext().
Example: UpdateContext({ varName: "Manoj" })

2. Global Variables (Set): Accessible throughout the entire app across all screens. Created using Set().
Example: Set(varCountry, "India")
