4. Collections and types of Collections in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Collections are groups of information or data it is used to store and manipulate multiple records within the app.
ğŸ‘‰ It helps improving app performance by handling temporary data locally without hitting the data source repeatedly.
ğŸ‘‰ Collections also support offline capabilities by storing data locally within the app.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Collections:
1. Collect() function: Creates a new collection or adds records to an existing one.
âœ… Example: Collect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice", Age: 25}) or using input controls like {Name: TextInput.Text, Age: Value(TextInput.Text)}

2. ClearCollect() function: Clears all existing records from a collection and adds a new records.
âœ… Example: ClearCollect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice1", Age: 20})

3. Clear() function: Removes all records from a collection.
âœ… Example: Clear(MyCollection)
