6. Cascading Dropdown in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ A Cascading Dropdown filter the options in one dropdown based on the selection made in another dropdown.
âœ… For Example: when a user selects a country, only the cities related to that country appear in the second dropdown.

âœ… Countryâ€“City scenario:
Dropdown 1 (Country) ---------> Items property: Distinct(CountriesCities, Country)
Dropdown 2 (City) ------------> Items property: Filter(CountriesCities, Country = Dropdown1.Selected.Result)
