7. Explain the concept of Delgations in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Delegation means pushing data operations like "filtering and sorting" to the data source instead of processing them inside Power Apps.
ğŸ‘‰ This is important when working with large datasets, like SharePoint lists with thousands of records.
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps has a default limit of 500 records (max 2000), so using non-delegable functions can cause incomplete or incorrect data results.
ğŸ‘‰ To avoid this, non-delegable functions are replaced with delegable ones like "Filter, Sort, and StartsWith", 
    ensuring efficient performance and accurate data retrieval.

ğŸ‘‰ This approach improved app speed, ensured data accuracy and delivers a better user experience.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

