13. What are the limitations of Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps is a powerful low-code tool, but it has some limitations we must consider.
ğŸ”¹ For example:
1. It can only retrieve 500â€“2000 records from a data source unless delegation is handled properly.
2. Complex UI customization are limited, and app performance can slow down with too many controls.
3. Offline functionality requires manual implementation.
4. Advanced features like premium connectors or Dataverse require extra licensing.
5. There is no built-in advanced debugging or Git-style version control.
